    "why": "31st August 2024\r\n\r\nRationale:\r\n\r\nAccording to the 2025 Medicines, Ethics, and Practice (MEP) guidelines, a use-by date indicates that the product must be used before the stated month begins. This means the medication is safe to use up to 31st August 2024. After this date, the product may no longer meet the required standards for quality, safety, or efficacy and should not be used.\r\n\r\nExplanation of other options:\r\n\r\nA) 1st August 2024:\r\nThis is incorrect. The medication can still be used throughout August 2024, so the last safe date is 31st August 2024.\r\n\r\nC) 1st September 2024:\r\nThis is incorrect. The use-by date 09/2024 means the product should not be used during September. Therefore, it is no longer safe to use by 1st September 2024.\r\n\r\nD) 30th September 2024:\r\nThis is incorrect. A use-by date of 09/2024 does not mean the product can be used until the end of September. It must not be used from the start of September 2024.\r\n\r\nE) 1st October 2024:\r\nThis is incorrect. The medication must not be used beyond 31st August 2024, so using it in October would not comply with MEP guidance.\r\n\r\nMedicines Use-by Date Guidance:\r\n\r\nMedicines with a use-by date must be used before the stated month begins, ensuring they meet the required standards of quality, safety, and efficacy. For a product with a use-by date of 09/2024, the last day it can be used is 31st August 2024. It is essential for pharmacists to verify this when preparing prescriptions to ensure patient safety.\r\n\r\nFor more information, refer to Chapter 3 of the MEP or visit the link below:\r\n\r\nhttps://preregshortcuts.com/courses/medicines-ethics-practice-course-mep",
