    "why": "**Keratitis** is an inflammation of the cornea caused by infections, trauma, or contact lens-related issues. Symptoms include severe eye pain, blurred vision, photophobia (sensitivity to light), and limbal redness (redness at the corneal-sclera border).\r\n\r\n**Risk factors for keratitis:**\r\n- Contact lens use, particularly with poor cleaning habits or extended wear, increases the risk. Improper daily cleaning, disinfection, and use of contaminated lens cases are common causes.\r\n  \r\n**Acanthamoeba keratitis**, a severe and painful infection, is particularly linked to soft lenses (especially reusable or extended wear). This condition can occur if lenses come into contact with tap water or are improperly disinfected, and requires prompt specialist treatment to prevent vision loss.\r\n\r\n**Prevention** involves strict compliance with lens care, avoiding tap water exposure, and limiting extended lens wear.\r\n\r\nCheck Image\r\nhttps://ibb.co/99g9xR0\r\n\r\nFor more information watch the OTC lesson on  Chapter 3 Opthalmology and Otology (Whooping Cough):\r\nhttps://preregshortcuts.com/courses/over-the-counter-medicines-course-otc",
